The actor is handsome, but his appereance seems totally different from Hardin's one. Plus, he looks like a good, sweet boy, but he should be a "bad boy" to play Hardin. I'm curious to see how this film turned out. How can a book full of sex scenes be a film? It would probably be a porn movie, not a movie. I also think that this whole situation is kinda ridiculous. There are so many beautiful, interesting books out there, and they choose the most dreadful. C'mon people, After is full of violence, people who have sex even if they don't love each other, awful parents-children relationships... However, Anna Todd is a good writer, she is strong on writing. After plot is very interesting and it could have been a very good book if it had been shortened and rewritten, mantaining the "basic plot" only. The plot is not banal: a bad boy who has been through hell who falls in love with a good girl who has suffered in her life. If it were developed in a better way, than it would be a good novel. But Anna Todd is still young, she will go on and I think she will be able to write a beautiful story.  However that's only my two cents on it.

text: I have to say something. See, this is a one minute teaser, not the full trailer. What you see here, is in no way anything you can expect from this movie. And the funny thing is, people are gonna see this movie anyway, just so they can say shit about it - well, I don't give a fuck, when you go and see this movie, we will get the second one, so you'll just make us happy. I hate to see how people think Fifty Shades of Grey is ''good'' and ''different'', yet, how toxic was *that* ? This book is so different from anything I've ever read. And you know why? Because I read all the books, because I didn't just read the first one. Because I didn't listen to what people told me about this book, I just went and read it to see for myself. The first book is just the start of something huge, a very emotional yet romantic rollercoaster. Yes, the first book has toxic elements. But that's exactly what Anna Todd (the writer) wanted to show. Some people are toxic. Some relationships start off toxic. There are people with shitty childhoods and trauma's, it fucks up who they are. There are people who can't love anyone. And Anna Todd wanted to show people what effect people can have on people. Tessa changed Hardin, in ways he never thought possible. And you guys have no clue how, because none of these haters have read every single word of the five books out there. You're basing your opinion on opinions you've heard on social media, on reading a few chapters, on reading the first book but nothing more, on the fact that this is ''based off a boyband and it's a fanfiction''. Who the fuck cares??? Aside from the fact that the only thing about One Direction she ever used were their names and their looks, I have a surprise for you, Fifty Shades was based off of Twilight: A FANFICTION. To All The Boys I've Loved Before, The Kissing Booth, Fifty Shades - they're all fanfiction turned into movies. The difference? This writer chose to discuss something that's different from other fanfiction for teenagers. She chose to discuss REAL PROBLEMS THAT SOME PEOPLE ACTUALLY GO THROUGH. Do I like Tessa and Hardin's relationship in the first book? God, no. I hate how Hardin drives her mad. I hate the influence he's got on her. I hate his intentions. BUT THAT'S THE POINT. Hate him! He's fucked up. You're hating him as much as Tessa does at first, as much as Noah does, as much as Tessa's mom does. You're hating Hardin as much as he hates himself. But that changes. The story changes. The intentions change. Hardin changes. Tessa changes. In the other books, it's not even about their mental influence on each other anymore. It's about who they are - and about who Tessa and Hardin help each other to become. But y'all haters didn't know this, did you? No, cause you've never even cared to read the whole story to understand anything about this. If you hate it so much and refuse to understand the story, then LEAVE. Don't watch this movie, don't watch this teaser, don't talk to the fandom. Don't bother, go somewhere else. If it's so bad, do all of us a favor and just leave. This movie is becoming a thing anyway and you can't do anything about it. Go give hate to something that actually deserves hate. Good day, everyone.

text: I don‚Äôt understand why it‚Äôs a problem to make a movie that portrays a toxic relationship? As long as it‚Äôs obvious that the relationship is toxic and is NOT romanticized and is given a proper rating to make sure it‚Äôs only seen by a certain age group then I don‚Äôt see what the problem is. Imagine someone making a movie about Hitler or some serial killer or other messed up things that happen IN REAL LIFE and have people be upset about it. Why? There are people analyzing movies and books everyday. They know the relationships being portrayed and they‚Äôre actively discussing them. This is just a normal part of life. Nothing is sunshine and rainbows all the time. If this movie is romanticizing the relationship then okay, that‚Äôs wrong. But if it‚Äôs NOT romanticizing it and is just portraying it as the toxic one that it is then I don‚Äôt see any problem. That‚Äôs just my opinion. Feel free to tell me what you think!

Your attitude towards a book that gains success is to throw shit on it. That‚Äôs ridiculous. It was based on Harry Styles years ago and the author always underlined that there was nothing but the figure of Harry. However I‚Äôd like to say that I‚Äôve already seen that some statements are different and the scenes in general as well. I know that a script cannot always be the perfect reflection of the book for so many reasons, but I find it strange and a little bit disappointing to see that things don‚Äôt go like you‚Äôd expect, because the magic isn‚Äôt the same anymore, and you just feel different. It‚Äôs like you are watching something that you don‚Äôt know about anymore. Obviously I‚Äôm talking as a fan of the trilogy. I hope that all other things and the plot in general would remain the same. The book is captivating not only for how it has been written but also because of the dynamic plot.

text: The relationship is toxic. Period. If you say otherwise, you don't understand abuse and I think that FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY, you should do research on physical/verbal and mental abuse because abuse is not just physical and Tessa wanting to be in the relationship does not change the fact that the relationship is abusive. To anyone saying it 'can be toxic at times' or anything along those lines, congrats! You've minimized abuse! To anyone saying it shouldn't be compared to 50 shades, you should know the author is a fan of the series. To anyone saying this shouldn't be associated with Harry Styles, you're trying to downplay the roots of the story so you don't feel embarrassed about enjoying this and you should remember a a chunk of the fans like the idea of this being a movie because they loved One Direction or they want to see Wattpad thrive. The movie can be different than the book. I'm not trying to bash anyone involved in the making of the book or the film, but the movie industry is seriously latched onto this toxic trope and they will continue to milk it the more it's consumed. They made this because it will rake in cash. The cycle continues.

text: Tbh I don't really think that Anna Todd wanted to romanticize abusive relationships. In the books, Tessa and the people around her, even Hardin, always recognize his (and hers, sometimes) obssessive and toxic behavior. Even tho the main point is the relationship between Tessa and Hardin, and they're certainly in love, the damaging conduct is never well seen - that's exactly why the relantionship continues to fall apart. Eventually, they do find a way to grow up and be better - for themselves and for each other. I'm NOT saying that if you're on a abusive relantionship you should stay and hope that it'll get better - no, you should definitely run the opposite direction. But i'm saying that there's no romantic point of view of what's bad in this relantionship, it is always pointed out and criticized.

text: everyone‚Äôs argument against why this isn‚Äôt a normal good-girl-bad-guy movie cliche is that the formerly abusive and cold male lead falls in love and decides to change for the person he loves and become a better person himself. That has literally happened in every other one of these stories, whether it be Divergent or Fifty Shades of Grey. You‚Äôre not proving your point at all and you‚Äôre further proving ours. The fact that the male lead had a messed up childhood is not and nowhere near justification for his actions and has been overdone to high hell, also notably in Fifty Shades. It‚Äôs nearly impossible for me to not view this as a less graphic version of Fifty Shades of Grey geared toward the teenage demographic. It was literally a wattpad fanfiction, and I‚Äôm sure it was the one that helped kick off the trope in modern young adult novels in the first place. There‚Äôs really no deeper meaning. It was an erotic fanfiction geared toward hormonal youth. That‚Äôs all there is to it. None of your white-knighting will change any of our opinions on it. We aren‚Äôt going to read it.

Just because he never hits her doesn‚Äôt mean he‚Äôs not abusive and just because she has a gentle, forgiving nature doesn‚Äôt excuse the fact that the girl needs some SERIOUS self worth work.  I get it. It‚Äôs a fantasy. It‚Äôs nice to read and it‚Äôs hot but I‚Äôll be damned if it‚Äôs nice in real life. Real life Hardin doesn‚Äôt live Tessa so much that he can‚Äôt keep away from her. Real life Hardin‚Äôs are insecure, selfish and cruel. Real life Hardins start off like this progress to beatings because Tessa didn‚Äôt have dinner ready on time 5 years down the track.  This kind of relationship isn‚Äôt cute and goals. It‚Äôs normal to be jealous and a little bit crazy. It‚Äôs not normal to break someone‚Äôs things because you‚Äôre angry at them. It‚Äôs not normal to forgive abuse and neglect because of sexual chemistry. For Christ‚Äôs sake, find a normal man and role play 50 Shades if that‚Äôs what you like. text: Can people in the comments stop hating After just because it was on Wattpad. There are actually a lot of good stories on Wattpad u people probably have never read. Don't blame the book or Wattpad for this cringe. The book is nothing like this cringy trailer for the movie. The problem is book to movie/Tv show adaptions are never really good or have the same tone. This trailer makes it seem like some cringy sexual college teen perfect romance all about sex when in actuality it was nothing like that in the book. Harry/Hardin had a lot of anger problems (took it out on people including tessa), got drunk a lot to forget his issues, hated his father who left him and his mother with all the money making them super poor and started a new family in america (which he hated them to for being to "perfect" and made a whole new "perfect" family) and hated how his mom lied to him about where his college money really came from (aka his rich dad who left them) since they were poor. He was always an asshole to tessa who was told by others that harry/hardin was no good he was just some bad boy who got drunk/partied and had sex to much but she didn't believe them and knew there had to be more to his story. She saw who he truly was an how they both were into literature (The scene in the trailer made it sexual but in the book he yells at her and gets mad that she is in his room touching his books no one knows he's into). In the beginning he would push her away and after a while of I hate u they started having sex but he was still an ass and was basically just using her because he lost trust in people along time ago so he didn't want to get to invested in someone who would leave him like everyone else. He didn't come to his senses and realize he loved her until after she had had enough of his drama and wanted no part with him. Later when they are actually a couple she tries to help him with his family problems. They live together and are dating until she finds out all this was some drunken bet at a party. (this was back when he was a drunken ass) The point is the book is not what the trailer makes it out to be. Don't blame Wattpad or the book in general (which is a lot more complex then the movie seems to be) when it's obvious the movie is what sucks! Book to movie or Tv show adaptions have a lot of times sucked and made a decent book seem cringy/awful when it really isn't.

As well as putting correct personalities and interests. I put him as an adult because he is 20 in real life. He is a business man who wants to be rich (succeeding after spending on mansion stuff he has $1,942,022), he is romantic, a musician and neat. I also spent 8 hours creating his mansion once he made a lot of money. I did use someone's mansion layout but the furniture, flowers, lighting stove, bathrooms are all created by me. I every night (once sister showed me how to keep screen from turning off) I left him on the max arrow forward and he made all the money on his own. I used 0 cheats on him. I think he would make an excellent edition to your characters. The hash tags used for Hero Fiennes: #Ellen395 #Hero #HeroFiennes For his Mansion if you want to put him in his home: #Ellen395 #Hero #HeroFiennes #HeroFiennesMansion #Bar #Pool #Garden #Fountain #Party Thank you for reading this you can comment on my Sims 4 Gallery who you want me to make next! text: Don't get me wrong. I think that it is great that erotica with substance do get their limelight moments, but to title this a great phenomen is definitely nonsense. I never understood why books such as Fifty Shades Of Grey and After sold out whilst books with important messages and questions remain in the shelves. I mean I am glad that women and men now do have the liberty to openly speak about sex, porn, kinks whatsoever. But I do not see a virtue, a value this movie tries to convey. Of course, not every movie has to have moral values, but I just do not understand why sexual stuff that is half-porn gets so hyped up. Live your life the way you want to, but this book or series is not considered literature by me in anyways. And before you ask, yes I actually tried to read the first book. It wasn't horrible per se, but you know unsubstantial. Same overused trope of good girl falling head over heels for the bad boy and his charms. This really shouldn't be celebrated as much as it gets. But congrats to the 10-15 years olds who are happy to finally get a movie.

text: I've actually had enough of hate comments about everything in general. But honestly now... Guys. This is all fictional.  Abusive relationship, you say...? NO RELATIONSHIP IS PERFECT. Each and every relationship has it's ups and downs, it's like a movie that might (or not) end sooner or later. And that's exactly what the writer tried to show - it's not a fairytale, it's simply a part of reality, the fact that nothing is like those stories with kissing a boy and then living happily ever after. No, it doesn't work like that. It never does. So if you got any more negative comments to say about this movie that will come out in April, about the book or maybe even about the author herself, just keep them for yourself.

text: BRO I LEGIT JUST WATCH THE MOVIE, I AM COMPLETE AND UTTERLY SHOOK IT GENUINELY SUCKS!!  I'm so upset and I don't even know why. I promise I am not trying to spread hate or bring down Anna Todd's work, but this movie was actually genuinely horrible! I can't even sugar coat it, people who say the movie was 'Amazing' are either completly lying or haven't read any of the books yet. Idk but for me, the movie was just all over the place, the characters were nothing like how they were portrayed in the books. FIRSTLY WHY IS HARDIN SO GOD DAMN NICE? When he was like "I'm sorry for the way I've treated lately" I was like hold up, homebody you've done absolutely nothing to her wdym mean you are sorry, and wtf is he apologising. Hardin Scott in the novels would never have apologised, let alone be nice to her throughout the beginning of their relationship!   EVEN MORE TEA! homegurl was mad because he said he doesn't want to date after 'everything they did,' they did nothing in the lake scene! If it wasn't for the book and knowing what they actually did in the lake scene, I would have never cared with they didn't decide to date because of all he did was tickle her arm and rub her tummy wtf! AND PLUS why was there no competition whatsoever with Zed aka Zayn, LIKE HE WAS SUPPOSED TO BE THAT HOT SWEETHEART, THAT MADE HARDIN MAD BECAUSE HE WAS ALWAYS A GENTLEMAN AND WAS ALWAYS ON THE VERGE OF STEALING HIS MRS!!!!!    HONESTLY! In my opinion, there was no storyline here or a great plot, the producers of this movie threw in a bunch of 'iconic' moments in the story and called it a day! which is completly a bad idea, there was no development of the relationships between the characters and it was just a bunch of random scenes in the movie like why tf were they even there. NOT TO MENTION, KAREN!!! KAREN WAS ADORABLE IN THE STORY AND THEY JUST MADE HER SOUND ALL STUCK UP AND STUFF! Tessa and Karen were supposed to be bff and then we get this awkward first impression, no hug or relationship at all scene and it was just hard to watch.   not even gonna lie this was the movie. THERE WERE TEN MILLION AWKWARD PAUSES IN EVERY SCENE LIKE NOBODY WAS TALKING THERE were JUST AWAKWARD MOMENTS OF SILENCE! Bro and they would have a small problem and straight after that they would be making out or in this case, Hardin would be hiding behind Tessa's thigh.    JUST PLEASE CONSIDER- IF U DONT READ THE BOOK YOU WILL BE A LOSTY AND NOT UNDERSTAND HALF THE THINGS GOING ON, SO PLEASE BE PREPARED FOR THAT! If you are planning to watch the movie still then please, by all means, watch it, but don't expect nothing but the same stuff in the trailer. I honestly loved the books, I have read every single one of them and they are just amazing. But even those who read it on watt pad the og's will be soooo upset. There is no plot or context behind these characters it's almost like they expect us to all the know the story before going in and watching this movie. There was nothing exciting about it (I mean except hero being shirtless for several minutes) But other than that, It was repetitive and not gonna lie straight-up boring.    I'm just so sad because I know this story and series is amazing, I wished more people knew about it but this story is not a good way to promote the story! Hardin was supposed to be broken at first, he was supposed to have a rude attitude and f**k around all the time, Not some perfect boy that says 'please' and 'thank you' and prayers with his family before he eats.   IM SO UPSET PLEASE IM BEGGING YOU PLEASE REMAKE THIS WHOLE MOVIE!! BECAUSE IF YOU WATCHED THE MOVIE AND THEN DECIDE TO READ THE BOOK, EVERYTHING WILL BE A SUPRISE TO U BECAUSE IT IS LEGIT TO DIFFERENT THINGS :(   p.s Where tf is the part when Hardin throws Tessa's notes everywhere scene and the zed and tessa scene and the night they spent at hardins fathers house and the internship office scenes and the showers scenes WHAT DO U MEAN THE ENTIRE BOOK IS MISSION FROM THE MOVIE IM SO SADDDDDD, I WANNA CRY IN A HOLE AND NEVER COME OUT UNTIL THEY MAKE A BETTER VERSIONNN   Please dont think this is hate, Just my opinion and the truth and the tea :)
